\begin_layout Itemize
Clewlow and Carverhill(1994) developed the general approach of using hedges(Gree
ks) as control variates。因为相对来说，hedged portfolio有更小的standard deviation，使用delta和ga
mma对冲可以有效降低组合的波动率。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At time T， the hedge consists of the savings account and the asset，which
 closely replicates the payoff of the option。可以用下式表达：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{t_{0}}e^{r(T-t_{0})}-[\Sigma_{i=0}^{N}(\frac{\partial C_{t_{i}}}{\partial S}-\frac{\partial C_{t_{i-1}}}{\partial S})S_{t_{i}}e^{r(T-t_{i})}]=C_{T}+\eta\tag{2.25}
\]

\end_inset

其中
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial C_{t_{-1}}}{\partial S}=\frac{\partial C_{t_{N}}}{\partial S}=0$
\end_inset

，
\begin_inset Formula $C_{t_{0}}$
\end_inset

是期权价格，
\begin_inset Formula $C_{T}$
\end_inset

是payoff，
\begin_inset Formula $\eta$
\end_inset

是hedge error。上式可以改写成
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{t_{0}}e^{r(T-t_{0})}+[\Sigma_{i=0}^{N-1}\frac{\partial C_{t_{i}}}{\partial S}(S_{t_{i+1}}-S_{t_{i}})e^{r(T-t_{i+1})}]=C_{T}+\eta\tag{2.26}
\]

\end_inset

delta对冲（方括号内的项）被称为delta-based martingale control variate 
\begin_inset Formula $cv_{1}$
\end_inset

且可以被表述为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
cv_{1}=\Sigma_{i=0}^{N-1}\frac{\partial C_{t_{i}}}{\partial S}(S_{t_{i+1}}-E[S_{t_{i}}])e^{r(T-t_{i+1})}
\]

\end_inset

于是，式(2.26)可以整理为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{t_{0}}e^{r(T-t_{0})}=C_{T}-\Sigma_{i=0}^{N-1}\frac{\partial C_{t_{i}}}{\partial S}(S_{t_{i+1}}-E[S_{t_{i}}])e^{r(T-t_{i+1})}+\eta\tag{2.28}
\]

\end_inset

(Clewlow and Strickland)解释为payoff的期望加上hedge等于期权价格按无风险利率的增长值。因此，可以利用上式进行模拟，最终得到期权
价值（方差更小）。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
同理可以使用gamma hedge control variate：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
cv_{2}=\Sigma^{N-1}\frac{\partial^{2}C_{t_{I}}}{\partial S^{2}}((\Delta S_{t_{i}})^{2}-E[(\Delta S_{t_{i}})^{2}]e^{r(T-t_{i+1})})\tag{2.29}
\]

\end_inset

其中，
\begin_inset Formula $E[(\Delta S_{t_{i}})^{2}]=S_{t_{i}}^{2}(e^{(2r+\sigma^{2})\Delta t_{i}}-2e^{r\Delta t_{i}}+1)$
\end_inset

，
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta S_{t_{i}}=S_{t_{i+1}}-S_{t_{i}}$
\end_inset

。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
令
\begin_inset Formula $t_{0}=0$
\end_inset

并假定存在
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

个control variates。则一般情况下，欧式call满足：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{0}e^{rT}=C_{T}-\Sigma_{k=1}^{n}\beta_{k}cv_{k}+\eta\tag{2.30}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Path-dependent valuation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
suppose we want to price a European-style claim of the underlying process,
 the payoff：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{T}=F(\{S_{t},0\leq t\leq T\})
\]

\end_inset

the risk-neutral pricing formula gives the price of the security at time
 0 as a discounted expectation：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{0}=e^{-rT}E_{0,S}^{Q}[F(\{S_{t},0\leq t\leq T\})]\tag{2.32}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
算法与之前的基本一致，只是计算payoff时需要考虑整个路径
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
以Asian option为例（payoff依赖于underlying asset在整个路径上的平均价格），即(以call为例)：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{T}=max(A_{T}-X,0)
\]

\end_inset

其中
\begin_inset Formula $A_{T}=\int_{t_{0}}^{T}S_{t}dt/(T-t_{0})$
\end_inset

【离散情况下：
\begin_inset Formula $A_{j+1}=(jA_{j}+S_{j+1})/(j+1)$
\end_inset

】
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Brownian bridge technique
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Intuitively, Brownian bridge is a stochastic interpolation between the initial
 state and the final state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
suppose the final condition of the stochastoc factor, say a stock price,
 is 
\begin_inset Formula $S(t)=S_{T}$
\end_inset

 at time T.
 假定
\begin_inset Formula $S(t)$
\end_inset

服从SDE：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
dS(t)=\mu S(t)dt+\sigma S(t)dZ(t)\tag{2.36}
\]

\end_inset

其解为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S(t)=S(0)exp((\mu-\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2})t+\sigma Z(t))\tag{2.37}
\]

\end_inset

我们可以使用式(2.1)进行Monte Carlo模拟，然而，在long-term simulations的情况下，模型会出现问题：因为当时期较长时，the
 drift dominates the volatility，此时drift 中的小误差会引起未来股价分布较大的误差。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the final condition at time T leads to a final condition for the Brownian
 motion at time T，which can be deduced from equation(2.37)：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(T)=\frac{1}{\sigma}(log(\frac{S(T)}{S(0)})-(\mu-\sigma^{2}/2)T)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
数学上，可以利用Brownian bridge 定义一个终值确定
\begin_inset Formula $z(T)$
\end_inset

的Wiener过程，如下：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
B(t)=z(0)+(z(T)-z(0))\frac{t}{T}+Z^{*}(t)-\frac{t}{T}Z^{*}(T)\tag{2.38}
\]

\end_inset

其中，
\begin_inset Formula $z(0)=0$
\end_inset

且
\begin_inset Formula $Z^{*}(t)$
\end_inset

是一个独立于
\begin_inset Formula $Z(t)$
\end_inset

的Wiener过程。于是，上式可以写为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
B(T)=(z(T)-Z^{*}(T))\frac{t}{T}+Z^{*}(t)\tag{2.39}
\]

\end_inset

将式(2.37)中的
\begin_inset Formula $Z(t)$
\end_inset

换成上面的Brownian bridge，其中，终值
\begin_inset Formula $z(T)=Z(T)$
\end_inset

得：
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
S(t) & =S(0)exp\{(\mu-\frac{\sigma^{2}}{2})t+(log(\frac{S(T)}{S(0)})-(\mu-\sigma^{2}/2)T)\frac{t}{T}+\sigma(Z^{*}(t)-\frac{t}{T}Z^{*}(T))\}\\
 & =S(0)exp(log(\frac{S(T)}{S(0)})\frac{t}{T}+\sigma(Z^{*}(t)-\frac{t}{T}Z^{*}(T)))\tag{2.40}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

式(2.40)不再包含之前的drift项
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

，Brownian bridge的drift由initial state 和 final state决定；但是一个新的问题也产生了：需要估计
\begin_inset Formula $S(T)$
\end_inset

（分布）
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
生成Brownian bridge（算法）
\end_layout

