\begin_layout Itemize
给定或生成
\begin_inset Formula $Z(T)$
\end_inset

，然后迭代计算子区间中间点上的值：具体如下：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(T)=\sqrt{T}\varepsilon_{1}\text{（若没有给定）}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(T/2)=Z(T)/2+\sqrt{T}/2\varepsilon_{2}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(T/4)=Z(T/2)/2+\sqrt{2T}\varepsilon_{3}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(3T/4)=[Z(T)+Z(T/2)]/2+\frac{\sqrt{2T}}{4}\varepsilon_{4}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vdots
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
更一般的情况，给定任意的中间点
\begin_inset Formula $t_{j}<t_{i}<t_{k}$
\end_inset

，以及两个已知的端点值
\begin_inset Formula $Z(t_{j})$
\end_inset

和
\begin_inset Formula $Z(t_{k})$
\end_inset

，则：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Z(t_{i})=(1-\gamma)Z(t_{j})+\gamma Z(t_{k})+\varepsilon\sqrt{\gamma(1-\gamma)(k-j)\Delta t}\tag{2.42}
\]

\end_inset

其中，
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma=(i-j)/(k-j)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Section
Jump-diffusion peocess and constant elasticity of variance diffusion model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
现实当中的许多数据需要引入一个随机的“jump”，Merton(1973)提出一个model：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dS}{S}=(\mu-\lambda\kappa)dt+\sigma dz+dq\tag{2.43}
\]

\end_inset

其中
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

是资产的期望收益，
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

是the rate (intensity) at which jumps occur，
\begin_inset Formula $\kappa$
\end_inset

是the average jump size measured as a proportional increase in the asset
 price，
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda\kappa$
\end_inset

是the average growth rate from the jumps。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Jump-diffusion 过程会产生厚尾（fat tails），相较于continuous lognormal diffusion过程来说，这点符合实际的资
产回报分布动态特征。Merton作了一个重要假设：the jump factor of the asset‘s return represents
 nonsystematic risk that can be hedged away。Consequently，a Black-Scholes
 type of portfolio must earn the risk-free rate since the uncertainty arising
 from geometric Brownian motion can be eliminated。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
如何生成Poisson随机变量
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
在Merton最简单的jump-diffusion model中，the logarithm of the size of the proportional
 jump has a normal distribution with a mean of 
\begin_inset Formula $-0.5\delta^{2}$
\end_inset

 and a standard deviation of 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

。In this case，a closed-form solution for European call option C exists：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C=\Sigma_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-\bar{\lambda}(\bar{\lambda}t)^{n}}}{n!}C_{n}(S,K,t,\bar{r},\sqrt{\sigma^{2}+\delta^{2}\frac{n}{t}})
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\lambda}=\lambda(1+\kappa)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{n}$
\end_inset

is 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

-th Black-Scholes option price with the instantaneous variance rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{\sigma^{2}+\delta^{2}\frac{n}{t}})$
\end_inset

 and risk-free rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{r}=r-\lambda\kappa+ln(1+\kappa)(n/t)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

